Now complete the JavaScript for the dashboard. The data is already loaded from
glue_data.json into these variables:
  DATA.schemas, DATA.tables, DATA.apps, DATA.usage

Implement the following functions:

STATE MANAGEMENT
  let state = {
    domain: null,     // selected schema id, or null for all
    app: null,        // selected SEAL ID, or null
    table: null,      // selected table id for detail drawer
    envs: new Set(),  // active env filters
    classes: new Set(),
    search: '',
    sort: 'reads'     // 'reads'|'name'|'cols'|'apps'
  }

getFilteredTables()
  - Filter DATA.tables by state.domain, state.app (only tables in that app),
    state.envs, state.classes, state.search (check table name, schema,
    consumer app names via lookup, SEAL IDs)
  - Sort by state.sort
  - Return filtered + sorted array

renderTables(tables)
  - Build table cards HTML and inject into #tableList
  - Update #center-count badge
  - Limit render to first 200, show "…and N more" message if truncated
  - Dim cards that don't match selectedApp if one is active

renderRightPanel(tables)
  - Aggregates: count unique apps, FIDs, SIDs, AWS roles, total reads
    across all usage records where tableId is in the visible tables set
  - LOBs: count apps per LOB from relevant apps, render sorted bars
  - Apps: list all apps that have at least 1 table in visible set,
    sorted by visible table count desc; clicking an app sets state.app
    and re-renders (acts as a filter)
  - FIDs: count usage records per FID for visible tables, show top 30
  - SIDs: same for SIDs

selectTable(id)
  - Set state.table, highlight card, open detail drawer
  - Populate drawer KPI grid and identity rows from DATA.usage
  - Clicking the same table again closes the drawer

selectDomain(id)
  - Set state.domain, clear state.app and state.table
  - Update domain tile active states (gold left border on active)
  - Re-render everything

selectApp(id)
  - Toggle: if already selected, deselect
  - Set state.app, re-render; tables not in this app become dimmed

buildMiniChart()
  - Small horizontal bar chart in left panel
  - One bar per schema, length = table count, coloured per schema colour
  - Rendered with Chart.js, height 130px

updateBreadcrumb()
  - "All Domains" (clickable → clearAll) / [Domain label] / App: [App Name]

updateKpiBanner()
  - Update the 6 KPI pills in the stats bar based on current visible tables

applyFilters() — master function that calls all of the above in order

Make all interactions feel instant (synchronous DOM updates, no loading spinners).
Ensure the right panel updates every single time any filter changes.
The dashboard should work completely offline once glue_data.json is in the
same folder as the HTML file.
